                "invention-title": [
                    "Preparation method of high-crystallinity polyheptylimide",
                    "一种高结晶性聚庚嗪酰亚胺的制备方法"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention relates to a method for preparing high-crystallinity polyheptylimide through heat treatment of rare earth oxide and metal salt, and belongs to the field of photocatalytic materials. A rare earth oxide and metal salt heat treatment process is utilized to realize regulation and control of a graphite phase carbon nitride crystal structure, and the problems of low crystallinity, many internal defects, difficult carrier migration, insufficient photocatalytic activity and the like of graphite phase carbon nitride as a functional material are solved. A metal salt is used as a template to provide catalytic action for precursor calcination polycondensation, so that graphite carbon nitride is converted from a melon structure to a PHI structure, and structural regulation and control of graphite phase carbon nitride are realized. The addition of the rare earth oxide can promote the deamination of the precursor in the calcination process, enhance the arrangement orderliness of in-plane and interlayer atoms of polyheptylimide (PHI), and improve the crystallinity of the PHI structure. According to the preparation method of the high-crystallinity polyheptylimide (PHI), the crystal structure of the polyheptylimide (PHI) can be regulated and controlled, the low crystallinity of graphite-phase carbon nitride is improved, internal defects are reduced, photon-generated carriers are promoted to be separated and migrated, expensive, toxic and harmful raw materials are not used in the preparation process, the research concept is green and environmentally friendly, and the method is suitable for industrial production. The material synthesis process is simple, commercial large-scale production is facilitated, and the material can be applied to the fields of photocatalytic degradation of organic pollutants, synthesis of hydrogen peroxide, photocatalytic hydrogen production or complete water splitting and the like."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明涉及稀土氧化物和金属盐热处理制备高结晶性聚庚嗪酰亚胺的方法，属于光催化材料领域。利用稀土氧化物和金属盐热处理过程，实现石墨相氮化碳晶体结构调控，解决石墨相氮化碳作为功能材料所面临的结晶度低、内部缺陷多、载流子迁移困难、光催化活性不足等问题。以金属盐为模板，为前驱体煅烧缩聚提供催化作用，使石墨氮化碳由melon结构向PHI结构转变，实现石墨相氮化碳的结构调控。稀土氧化物的加入能够促进前驱体在煅烧过程中脱氨，增强聚庚嗪酰亚胺(PHI)面内和层间原子排布的有序性，提高了PHI结构的结晶性。本发明所提供高结晶性聚庚嗪酰亚胺(PHI)的制备方法，能够实现聚庚嗪酰亚胺(PHI)晶体结构调控，改善石墨相氮化碳的低结晶度，降低内部缺陷，促进光生载流子分离和迁移，在制备过程中未使用昂贵、有毒有害的原材料，研究理念绿色环保，材料合成过程简单，有利于商业化大规模生产，可应用于光催化降解有机污染物、合成过氧化氢，光催化产氢或全解水等领域。"
                }
